<br>
I used VMware to run linux originally. VMware works well, both ways round. But you have 2 OS's using processor time, which is obviously bad. Also, control over hardware is still pushed thru the host OS.<br>
<br>
Games are all written for DX / Win2k/XP nowdays. Don't even think you will have it working well under linux, realistically. Doesn't stop you only installing xp (or something) in minimal config and then only installing games, removing as you finish with them.<br>
<br>
